  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the amount is relatively modest ($25,000), and the defendant has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. The outburst from the spectator is legally irrelevant and was excluded from the sentencing determination. A short-term custodial sentence is balanced against the defendant's character and the nature of the offense.",
